
Secure Notes API

A Flask REST API that allows users to register, login, and manage personal notes securely using JWT authentication. Each user can only access and modify their own notes.

Features
User registration and login
JWT authentication
Secure password hashing (Flask-Bcrypt)
Full CRUD operations for notes
Route protection (user-specific data access)
Pagination support
Tech Stack

Python, Flask, Flask-RESTful, Flask-JWT-Extended, Flask-Migrate, Flask-Bcrypt, SQLAlchemy, SQLite

Project Structure
app.py
models.py
migrations/
resources/
 ├── auth.py
 └── notes.py
Installation
git clone <repo-url>
cd <project-folder>
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install flask flask-restful flask-migrate flask-jwt-extended flask-bcrypt flask-sqlalchemy
Database Setup
flask db init
flask db migrate -m "initial migration"
flask db upgrade
Run Application
python app.py

Server runs at:

http://127.0.0.1:5000
Authentication Endpoints

POST /register – Create user account
POST /login – Get JWT token

Notes Endpoints (Protected)

GET /notes?page=1 – Get user notes (paginated)
POST /notes – Create note
PATCH /notes/<id> – Update note
DELETE /notes/<id> – Delete note

Rules
Users only access their own notes
JWT required for all notes routes
Passwords are securely hashed
Error Codes

400 – Bad Request
401 – Unauthorized
404 – Not Found
500 – Server Error

